{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf0393397-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s8354"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8354"},"text":"§ 8354.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Expenditures for cooperative agreements to lease aircraft","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"On and after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-11-10"},"text":"November 10, 2005","children":[],"tail":", notwithstanding any other provision of law, the Secretary of Agriculture may use appropriations available to the Secretary for activities authorized under sections 8351 to 8353 "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002365"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002365"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See Reference in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title, under this or any other Act, to enter into cooperative agreements, with a State, political subdivision, or agency thereof, a public or private agency, organization, or any other person, to lease aircraft if the Secretary determines that the objectives of the agreement will: (1) serve a mutual interest of the parties to the agreement in carrying out the programs administered by the Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service, Wildlife Services; and (2) all parties will contribute resources to the accomplishment of these objectives; award of a cooperative agreement authorized by the Secretary may be made for an initial term not to exceed 5 years."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf0393398-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/97/tVII/s749"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–97, title VII, § 749","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 2005","children":[],